    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo i just finished replacing the brake pads on my 2018 camry but now when i drive it i keep hearing this really high pitched squealing noise when i hit the brakes. not sure if i messed up or if it's a sensor or a stuck caliper. what do u think?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A high-pitched squeal after brake pad replacement often points to a few common issues. It could be related to the new pads themselves, perhaps they need a bedding-in period, or there might be an issue with the rotor surface. Sometimes, a small piece of debris gets caught between the pads and rotor, which can cause that high-pitched sound. I recommend checking if the calipers are moving freely and ensuring the hardware clips are installed correctly.",
