    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i checked the clips and they seem fine. the squeal is pretty constant though, almost like a piercing scream right when the pedal goes down. i was thinking maybe the caliper is sticking a bit? how can i tell for sure if it's a stuck caliper versus just a bad sensor or something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the noise is a constant, piercing scream, a sticking caliper is a strong possibility, especially if the pads are rocking unevenly. To check for a sticking caliper, try spinning the wheels by hand when the car is securely parked; if one side feels significantly tighter or resists turning more than the other, that caliper is likely sticking. If the wheels turn freely, you might want to inspect the caliper slide pins to ensure they are clean and lubricated, which is another common culprit for noise.",
      "source": "target",
