    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it feels like the wheel turns okay but the sound is just so weird and random, sometimes it's louder than others. i'm starting to get a bit paranoid that i missed something obvious or like there's something wrong with the hardware that i just can't see. is there any other way to troubleshoot this without taking everything apart again?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the wheel spins fine but the noise is intermittent, the issue might be less about major sticking and more about surface interaction or vibration. Try listening very closely to see if the sound changes when you apply light versus firm pressure; sometimes, a very slight misalignment or a piece of fine debris can cause this. Another quick check is to inspect the rotor surface for any scoring or uneven wear, even if the pads are new.",
      "source": "target",
